5
00:01:47,798 --> 00:01:50,120
 The door has been unlocked. Please come in. 

6
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:53,059
You go first. I'll go after you.

7
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,840
Mom.

8
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,959
We're back.

9
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:12,680
How did you two end up coming home together?

10
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,960
We ran into each other at the entrance. Where's Dad?

11
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:19,740
He's gone to Xiao Xiao's place. He'll probably stay there for dinner.

12
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:23,080
I was sweating in the car just now. I'll go upstairs and get changed.

13
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,200
I'm going upstairs as well.

14
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,100
Hurry up.

15
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:57,619
Mom.

16
00:03:57,619 --> 00:03:59,241
Where are my wood carvings?

17
00:03:59,241 --> 00:04:01,360
I told the cleaner to get rid of them.

18
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,680
Why?

19
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,319
I told you before

20
00:04:04,319 --> 00:04:06,400
that I dislike it when you mess with those things.

21
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,560
Wood shavings cover the floor. It's so filthy.

22
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,840
You're a girl. Can't you find a better hobby?

23
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:11,908
Mom, Qin Qinâ€”

24
00:04:11,908 --> 00:04:15,055
I don't like that you're a doctor either.

25
00:04:15,055 --> 00:04:18,120
It's a hard and thankless job, plus you have to work overtime.

26
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,560
When you have a family,

27
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,480
how are you going to take care of them?

28
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:23,280
Mom. Iâ€”

29
00:04:25,704 --> 00:04:26,600
Auntie.

30
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,840
Xiao Xiao, you're here.

31
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:29,701
I'm here for a free dinner.

32
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:33,899
All right, you young ones chat.

33
00:04:42,219 --> 00:04:45,119
What's wrong? Did someone get scolded again?

34
00:05:13,915 --> 00:05:17,755
 - It's break time. Let's grab some food. 
 - Sure. 

35
00:05:21,379 --> 00:05:22,519
Old Jiang!

36
00:05:22,519 --> 00:05:24,019
Yes, Captain?

37
00:05:26,026 --> 00:05:27,599
Who's in charge of trash disposal today?

38
00:05:27,599 --> 00:05:28,959
Dapeng is on duty today.

39
00:05:28,959 --> 00:05:31,199
I saw him go downstairs to take out the trash already.

40
00:05:31,199 --> 00:05:34,201
Did you lose something important? I'll help you look for it.

41
00:05:34,201 --> 00:05:35,839
I'm just asking.

42
00:05:35,839 --> 00:05:38,760
Okay, it's fine. You may leave now.

43
00:05:44,799 --> 00:05:48,720
If you decide to change cooks, inform me beforehand. I'll hire them for sure.

44
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,520
My mom is here.

45
00:05:52,652 --> 00:05:54,519
You scared me!

46
00:05:54,519 --> 00:05:56,759
Aren't you the one who's most afraid of her?

47
00:05:56,759 --> 00:05:58,160
I recently opened a new bar.

48
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:01,220
Come to my place tomorrow. You two can relax a bit.

49
00:06:03,140 --> 00:06:04,380
Mom.

50
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:06,079
Not again!

51
00:06:06,079 --> 00:06:07,600
Are you in the habit of scaring me now?

52
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,639
Auntie is undeniably a big devil,

53
00:06:09,639 --> 00:06:11,881
but she's also adorable. Am I right?

54
00:06:11,881 --> 00:06:15,939
I was telling them that I hadn't seen you for days and missed you.

55
00:06:15,939 --> 00:06:17,239
Here.

56
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,960
You two aren't observant at all.

57
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,160
Take a seat.

58
00:06:28,639 --> 00:06:30,279
Yanchen,

59
00:06:30,279 --> 00:06:35,000
you should learn from Xiao Xiao and get yourself a partner soon.

60
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,079
You all grew up together.

61
00:06:37,079 --> 00:06:40,079
You should become a good influence on him.

62
00:06:40,079 --> 00:06:44,000
What if he takes my advice but ends up finding someone you don't like?

63
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,439
If she's not good, of course, she's not acceptable.

64
00:06:45,439 --> 00:06:47,841
If so, define what's good and what's not.

65
00:06:47,841 --> 00:06:49,509
First and foremost,

66
00:06:49,509 --> 00:06:52,279
never marry someone who's unequal in social status.

67
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:54,599
That's a big "no."

68
00:06:54,599 --> 00:06:56,040
Here.

69
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,852
This is for you.

70
00:06:58,839 --> 00:07:00,620
And this...

71
00:07:00,620 --> 00:07:03,480
Oh, there are red envelopes. I want one, too. 
   (TN: usually filled with money) 

72
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:05,179
You don't need it.

73
00:07:05,179 --> 00:07:08,995
Those are a few ladies I chose for you,

74
00:07:08,995 --> 00:07:12,079
and those are a few men I chose for you.

75
00:07:12,079 --> 00:07:16,720
Take a look and see if you set your eyes on any of them.

76
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:18,238
Then let me know.

77
00:07:18,238 --> 00:07:19,939
Okay?

78
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:21,299
Got it.

79
00:07:21,299 --> 00:07:23,099
Let's eat.

80
00:07:29,472 --> 00:07:31,720
I don't want to bring this up,

81
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,787
but you two should come home more often.

82
00:07:33,787 --> 00:07:36,160
It's a big house, yet it's so quiet.

83
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,760
Am I right?

84
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,759
Also, Qin'er,

85
00:07:49,759 --> 00:07:52,759
you work at the hospital. It must be tiring.

86
00:07:52,759 --> 00:07:55,720
Come to my bar when you're free. I'll open a bottle of good wine for you.

87
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:59,819
And you... You should come along, too.

88
00:07:59,819 --> 00:08:01,720
Isn't Auntie trying to find you a partner?

89
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:04,000
My bar is full of pretty girls.

90
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,580
- I can hook you up with them. 
 - Xiao Xiao.

91
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:12,179
Keep quiet when you're eating.

92
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,698
What are you looking for?

93
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:47,180
A lighter.

94
00:08:49,519 --> 00:08:51,479
She gave it to you?

95
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:58,104
You carried it everywhere for the past ten years.

96
00:08:58,104 --> 00:09:00,039
Since you care about her so much,

97
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:02,259
why did you two break up in the first place?

98
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:28,639
There's a huge gap between our families.

99
00:09:28,639 --> 00:09:31,400
Her parents strongly emphasize social status and family background.

100
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,960
They think I'm not good enough for her.

101
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:39,279
I think I understand that.

102
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:41,720
You've been really hard on yourself all these years.

103
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,600
You always want to be first in everything.

104
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:46,120
You bear the honor and the mission on your shoulders.

105
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:48,719
I bet she's part of the reason.

106
00:09:51,399 --> 00:09:54,292
I want to bring us closer together.

107
00:09:54,292 --> 00:09:58,165
I've previously fantasized that one day,

108
00:09:58,165 --> 00:10:00,467
if I meet her again,

109
00:10:01,735 --> 00:10:06,094
I can stand proudly in front of her.

110
00:10:10,399 --> 00:10:12,099
I'm fine.

111
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:15,126
For the past ten years,

112
00:10:17,448 --> 00:10:19,928
I've always carried that lighter with me.

113
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:24,799
Don't you think it's weird?

114
00:10:24,799 --> 00:10:26,475
She's here now,

115
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,199
but I've lost it.

116
00:10:32,279 --> 00:10:36,140
For some reason, I feel empty inside.

117
00:10:42,679 --> 00:10:45,979
I don't know exactly what happened between you two,

118
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:48,440
but I can tell...

119
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:51,739
you were badly hurt because of that relationship.

120
00:10:53,679 --> 00:10:55,320
You've seen her anyway.

121
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:59,159
Since you don't want to bring up the past, you should let it go.

122
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:02,320
There's no need to search for some things once they're lost.

123
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:05,279
If you missed out on someone, there's no need to go back.

124
00:11:05,279 --> 00:11:07,640
Don't live in the past.

125
00:11:11,304 --> 00:11:15,480
Perhaps it's a sign from Heaven for you to let go of the past

126
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:17,550
and start a new life.

127
00:11:35,399 --> 00:11:37,500
Help me out with this.

128
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,600
All of them look good.

129
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:49,540
Don't you think... they all look alike?

130
00:11:49,540 --> 00:11:52,080
It seems their features have been refined.

131
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:55,220
They're not even close to you.

132
00:12:02,919 --> 00:12:04,420
Jiang Yu?

133
00:12:04,420 --> 00:12:07,400
He's a decent man. He's reliable.

134
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:09,320
Compared to Song...

135
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:11,120
he's way better.

136
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,434
What's wrong?

137
00:12:14,434 --> 00:12:16,369
Can't I share my view without being asked?

138
00:12:16,369 --> 00:12:18,519
I'm not afraid of your anger.

139
00:12:18,519 --> 00:12:20,907
You two aren't compatible. It wouldn't work.

140
00:12:20,907 --> 00:12:24,779
We always look at the past in a favorable way.

141
00:12:24,779 --> 00:12:26,679
Actually, you're not in love with him.

142
00:12:26,679 --> 00:12:28,919
You merely have regrets about the past.

143
00:12:28,919 --> 00:12:32,940
It's human nature to feel like things we can't have are better.

144
00:12:37,056 --> 00:12:39,993
- It's so late. Where are you going? 
 - The bar.

145
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:58,559
Welcome, pretty doctor. The bar owner is personally here to receive you.

146
00:12:58,559 --> 00:13:00,600
Save your effort to coax your girlfriend instead.

147
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:03,599
- You're my one and only girlfriend. 
 - Get off.

148
00:13:03,599 --> 00:13:05,720
You hit too hard!

149
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,559
She's rude. You should educate her.

150
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:09,720
Stop talking nonsense. Show us around.

151
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:12,292
All right. President Meng, this way, please.

152
00:13:12,292 --> 00:13:13,427
Come on.

153
00:13:14,361 --> 00:13:15,679
What do you think? Not bad, right?

154
00:13:15,679 --> 00:13:17,019
Boss.

155
00:13:17,019 --> 00:13:18,679
Bring me three glasses of Yamazaki 25.

156
00:13:18,679 --> 00:13:20,960
- Okay, sure. 
 - Take a seat.

157
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:23,039
Here, Qin'er.

158
00:13:23,039 --> 00:13:24,739
Take a seat.

159
00:13:26,267 --> 00:13:28,839
I bought two floors in total. The upper floor is always crowded.

160
00:13:28,839 --> 00:13:31,039
This floor is slightly quieter, though.

161
00:13:31,039 --> 00:13:33,595
The view isn't bad, right?

162
00:13:33,595 --> 00:13:34,840
It's not bad, indeed.

163
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:37,519
I didn't expect you to actually have good taste.

164
00:13:37,519 --> 00:13:39,751
I learned it from you.

165
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:44,280
Qin'er, you should come whenever you're free.

166
00:13:57,804 --> 00:13:58,960
What's wrong with you?

167
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,360
Are you new?

168
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:02,899
Haven't you received any training before?

169
00:14:02,899 --> 00:14:05,080
Boss, she's newly hired. I'm really sorry.

170
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:06,720
Hurry, apologize.

171
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:08,120
I'm sorry.

172
00:14:08,120 --> 00:14:09,320
It's fine.

173
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:12,700
She's just a part-timer. I'll definitely talk to her later.

174
00:14:19,143 --> 00:14:21,840
Thorough training and proper guidance are important, especially for part-timers.

175
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:23,564
This is a mistake in your work, got it?

176
00:14:23,564 --> 00:14:26,066
I'm sorry. I'll pay more attention going forward.

177
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:29,579
The fire department will be here for an inspection later.

178
00:14:29,579 --> 00:14:31,720
Please handle the reception. Be polite to them.

179
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:34,940
All right, I'll get back to it then.

180
00:14:34,940 --> 00:14:36,919
You're really strict.

181
00:14:36,919 --> 00:14:39,940
You're not just pretending for us, are you?

182
00:14:39,940 --> 00:14:43,799
I'm serious and dedicated regarding work, okay?

183
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:45,934
I need to make a call.

184
00:14:49,759 --> 00:14:52,299
It's not easy to hire employees these days.

185
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:05,000
I'm sorry.

186
00:15:12,919 --> 00:15:16,060
Do you think she looks like Qin'er a bit?

187
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:17,459
Does she?

188
00:15:17,459 --> 00:15:19,540
I think they look alike.

189
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:40,080
Do you regularly inspect the fire safety equipment here?

190
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:41,480
We do.

191
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:43,879
If there are any issues, remember to replace them promptly.

192
00:15:43,879 --> 00:15:46,720
Don't worry. We'll certainly follow the regulations strictly.

193
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:50,260
Hello. Are you from the fire department?

194
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:52,019
Yes.

195
00:15:52,019 --> 00:15:55,619
Fire inspections are typically conducted by firefighters, aren't they?

196
00:15:55,619 --> 00:15:57,159
Fire inspections are under the fire brigade's jurisdiction.

197
00:15:57,159 --> 00:16:00,660
Firefighters belong to Fire and Rescue and aren't in charge of inspections.

198
00:16:01,761 --> 00:16:03,076
Show us the way to the emergency exit.

199
00:16:03,076 --> 00:16:05,336
Sure. This way, please.

200
00:16:29,519 --> 00:16:31,319
What are you thinking about?

201
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:36,519
Two days ago, I ran into Song Yan.

202
00:16:37,399 --> 00:16:38,679
What does he do for a living?

203
00:16:38,679 --> 00:16:40,066
Wait, let me guess.

204
00:16:40,066 --> 00:16:42,519
Don't tell me he's self-employed, like me.

205
00:16:42,519 --> 00:16:44,479
He's a firefighter.

206
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:47,759
Then what?

207
00:16:47,759 --> 00:16:49,360
Did you chat and reminisce together?

208
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:51,380
How did the conversation go?

209
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,460
He ignored me.

210
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:58,640
So you feel a sense of regret?

211
00:16:59,986 --> 00:17:01,720
Whether I did or didn't,

212
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:04,087
there's nothing I can do.

213
00:17:04,087 --> 00:17:06,820
Life is full of regrets.

214
00:17:06,820 --> 00:17:09,559
Even if people try hard and give their all

215
00:17:09,559 --> 00:17:13,060
as if they've lost their minds, in the end...

216
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:17,000
no one can escape difficulties.

217
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,072
So many years have passed.

218
00:17:19,072 --> 00:17:21,076
I can't believe you still like him.

219
00:17:22,599 --> 00:17:24,919
I thought I didn't anymore.

220
00:17:31,260 --> 00:17:33,386
But you couldn't control it once you saw him.

221
00:17:33,386 --> 00:17:36,279
It seems your feelings for him flared up again.

222
00:17:36,279 --> 00:17:38,880
It means you've never forgotten him.

223
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:42,995
Qin'er, the most tormenting thing in this world is to refuse to move on,

224
00:17:42,995 --> 00:17:44,500
thinking that you can go back.

225
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:46,232
I've heard the story between you two.

226
00:17:46,232 --> 00:17:48,319
I don't mean to be rude,

227
00:17:48,319 --> 00:17:52,459
but if it was impossible in the past, it's even more impossible in the future.

228
00:17:53,859 --> 00:17:55,640
Cheer up. Don't think about it.

229
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:58,279
Let's go. Let's grab some drinks.

230
00:17:58,279 --> 00:18:01,220
Go ahead. I need to wash my hands.

231
00:18:24,319 --> 00:18:25,819
 No peeping. 

232
00:18:51,359 --> 00:18:53,759
Qin'er, where are you going?

233
00:18:53,759 --> 00:18:56,499
Something came up at the hospital. I need to go now.

234
00:18:57,359 --> 00:18:59,459
G-Go?

235
00:19:04,039 --> 00:19:06,979
Not only did Qin'er leave, but she also lied.

236
00:19:09,448 --> 00:19:12,319
- What's wrong? 
 - Do you know what Qin'er told me just now?

237
00:19:12,319 --> 00:19:15,079
"Life is full of regrets."

238
00:19:15,079 --> 00:19:18,279
"Even if people try hard and give their all..."

239
00:19:18,279 --> 00:19:20,080
"no one can escape difficulties."

240
00:19:20,080 --> 00:19:22,761
No one in their right mind would say that.

241
00:19:28,119 --> 00:19:30,039
Life is short.

242
00:19:30,039 --> 00:19:33,500
Being able to enjoy pleasures is already a great blessing.

243
00:19:36,039 --> 00:19:39,720
Giving up what you already have to pursue something elusive and intangible

244
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,488
is not worth it.

245
00:19:55,839 --> 00:19:57,599
- Hello. 
 - Hello.

246
00:19:57,599 --> 00:20:00,620
May I ask if Song Yan works here?

247
00:20:00,620 --> 00:20:02,200
May I ask who you are?

248
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:04,759
I'm... his former classmate.

249
00:20:04,759 --> 00:20:06,359
Can you help me get in touch with him?

250
00:20:06,359 --> 00:20:08,719
- Please wait a moment. 
 - Thank you.

251
00:20:11,279 --> 00:20:12,359
Hello, Captain Song?

252
00:20:12,359 --> 00:20:15,819
Someone's looking for you out front. She claims to be your former classmate.

253
00:20:17,599 --> 00:20:19,319
May I know your name?

254
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:20,888
Xu Qin.

255
00:20:20,888 --> 00:20:23,268
Her name is Xu Qin, Captain.

256
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:28,560
Sure.

257
00:20:29,559 --> 00:20:33,240
I'm sorry. Captain Song isn't in today.

258
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:34,519
Where did he go?

259
00:20:34,519 --> 00:20:36,780
He probably...

260
00:20:36,780 --> 00:20:38,940
went out for training.

261
00:20:41,079 --> 00:20:42,540
Thank you.

262
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:55,119
- Li Cheng. 
 - Yes, Staff Officer Li?

263
00:20:55,119 --> 00:20:57,960
